{
  "enabled": true,
  "name": "AKR Knowledge Reminder",
  "description": "Reminds the agent about the AKR knowledge repository on every prompt, triggering a fetch for relevant prior knowledge before responding.",
  "version": "1",
  "when": {
    "type": "promptSubmit"
  },
  "then": {
    "type": "askAgent",
    "prompt": "You have access to the Agent Knowledge Repository (AKR) — a shared knowledge base that persists learnings across interactions. Evaluate the user's request and determine if prior knowledge could be useful. Lean towards YES — when in doubt, fetch. The ONLY time you should skip is for trivial, self-contained requests that clearly need no context (e.g. 'format this line', 'add a comma here', 'what time is it').\n\nIf you determine prior knowledge could help, complete these steps in order before responding:\n1. Read `.kiro/steering/agent-knowledge.md` into context for full AKR usage rules and command reference.\n2. Run `akr-fetch --query \"<brief summary of the user's request>\"` to retrieve relevant prior knowledge.\n\nAlso, if during the interaction you discover something worth remembering (bug fix patterns, architectural decisions, code patterns, dependency insights), use `akr-commit` to persist it. The steering file has the full command reference.\n\nDo not ask the user for permission to run these steps. Execute them silently."
  }
}